thrust coupling?

18:30.068 --> 18:32.320
(quietly): I don't know
which one we'll go with,

18:32.362 --> 18:35.323
but they both blew
the fuckin' doors off McMillan.

18:35.365 --> 18:39.327
Yeah, that guy
from McMillan's weird, man.

18:39.369 --> 18:42.997
He really sucked the other day.

18:43.039 --> 18:46.251
SPEAKER: ...and torque-supported
tensile freighting.

18:47.836 --> 18:50.922
Do you know where your son is?

18:50.964 --> 18:53.591
-Which one?
-John Tavner.

18:53.633 --> 18:56.970
-Yes.
-Where is John Tavner?

18:57.011 --> 18:59.347
He's at Fort Meade
teaching a class

18:59.389 --> 19:02.183
on classic
army battlement infrastructure

19:02.225 --> 19:04.769
and the economy of war.

19:04.811 --> 19:08.731
-In the United States?
-Yes.

19:08.773 --> 19:10.567
He teaches college?

19:10.608 --> 19:12.569
He's an instructor
for the United States Army.

19:12.610 --> 19:14.612
He teaches
whatever they ask him to.

19:14.654 --> 19:17.532
That's what he's teaching now.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.119
Call them.

19:22.537 --> 19:24.497
Were you, earlier today,

19:24.539 --> 19:26.708
in a room
in the Sansille East Hotel

19:26.749 --> 19:28.918
in the 10th arrondissement
of Paris?

19:28.960 --> 19:30.920
-No.
-Where were you?

19:30.962 --> 19:32.964
Renting a tuxedo.

19:33.006 --> 19:34.966
AGATHE:
In order to...?

19:35.008 --> 19:37.802
In order to attend
the wedding of my son.

19:37.844 --> 19:40.138
My other son. In Paris.

19:40.179 --> 19:44.726
And in order to look nice,
I guess, while I'm doing that.

19:47.520 --> 19:49.856
His name?

19:49.898 --> 19:51.608
Edward...

19:51.649 --> 19:53.276
Tavner.

19:55.737 --> 19:59.073
-That's why you are in Paris?
-Yes.

20:00.909 --> 20:03.077
The setting of this wedding?

20:03.119 --> 20:05.330
TOM:
The Chapel of Saint Michael.

20:05.371 --> 20:07.040
The date?

20:08.249 --> 20:10.543
(sighs):
Seven hours from now.

20:10.585 --> 20:11.920
So...

20:16.174 --> 20:18.259
Our countries are
on good terms--

20:18.301 --> 20:20.386
